FT  02 OCT 92 / World Trade News: Beijing to retain US trade status
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NANCY DUNNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CHINA is set to retain its low-tariff most favoured nation (MFN) status in
trade with the US, following a vote in the Senate yesterday which sustained
by a 59-40 vote a presidential veto of legislation attaching conditions to
its status.
This follows a 345-74 vote in the House on Wednesday in favour of placing
conditions on China's status. A two-thirds majority is needed in both houses
for this to stand.
The attempt to use trade as leverage with China to improve its human rights
policies has picked up support in both houses since the Tiananmen Square
pro-democracy protests were crushed. But the White House argues the US has
more influence over China if it keeps close trade ties.
</TEXT>
