<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 92 / International Company News: Chevron expects Dollars 375m
gain from settlement
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CHEVRON, one of the biggest US oil and gas groups, yesterday said it
expected to record a fourth-quarter extraordinary gain of Dollars 375m
following settlement of its litigation with Pennzoil.
Under the agreement, Pennzoil will acquire a group of Chevron's US oil and
gas fields in a tax-free exchange of stock.
The deal will reduce Pennzoil's stake in Chevron to about 5.3 per cent, or
about 17.2m shares, from about 9.7 per cent.
Chevron's litigation with Pennzoil started in 1989, when Pennzoil's stake in
Chevron reached 9 per cent.
Once the deal is completed, both companies will drop all legal claims
against each other stemming from Pennzoil's 1989 investment.
In addition, both companies have agreed not to purchase additional shares of
each other's stock for five years.
</TEXT>
