FT  01 OCT 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Market in Australia is keeping firm in the face of continuing currency
volatility. The US and Australian dollars have been taking a downward course
against Europe and Japan. In every wool-using country currency has become
far more important in affecting prices from day to day than the course of
the wool market itself. International relationships among companies and with
suppliers and customers confuse the issue, and trading increasingly
cautious. The Australian Wool Corporation's market indicator on September 30
was 533c a kg., just one cent higher than a week before.
