<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 92 / Utilities failing on complaints
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PUBLIC utilities are unacceptably bad at handling consumers' complaints,
according to the latest issue of Which?, the Consumers' Association
magazine.
A survey of subscribers that had complained to utilities found that British
Telecom and British Rail were worst at handling complaints, but no utility
came out well. For every utility more people were dissatisfied with the
handling of their complaint than were satisfied.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 11
</PAGE>
</DOC>
