<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 92 / Thames Riverbus wins a reprieve
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RIVERBUS, THE loss-making Thames passenger service running between central
London and Docklands, won a temporary reprieve yesterday, hours before it
was due to close at midnight.
The administrators of Olympia &amp; York's Canary Wharf development in Docklands
and other interested parties have agreed to keep the service for up to a
month to allow time for negotiations with the government over Canary Wharf's
future.
</TEXT>
