<BYLINE>
   By DAMIEN FRASER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Pedro Aspe, Mexico's finance minister, expects growth for the whole of
this year to be similar to that in the first half - about 2.8 per cent and
so even lower than yesterday's latest OECD forecast, itself revised
downwards. He anticipated an increase in growth in the first quarter of next
