increased the pensioners' desperation.
Argentina has about 4m pensioners whose benefits consume 7 per cent of gross
domestic product. The government has refused to increase the minimum pension
of the equivalent of Dollars 150 a month because it says the public pension
fund is bankrupt. It is working on a pensions reform, replacing state
benefits with private ones.
